  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Treatment of acetabular fractures needs a perfect diagnosis to anticipate surgical
      difficulties. E. Letournel described a rare atypical both-column fracture which &quot; introduces
      enormous surgical difficulties &quot;. Its particularity is a sagittal comminution interesting the
      acetabular roof.

      In this experience the particular fracture is probably under-diagnosed. The purpose of this
      study is to give the exact incidence and a precise description of these fractures to improve
      their surgical management.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
